<page_title>Placing a &quot;Close&quot; button on a pop-up window</page_title>
<text> Placing a &quot;Close&quot; button on a pop-up window

When you design a hyperlink that can open up a new window, you often want to also place a &quot;Close&quot; button in the new window so that the user can conveniently close it. Although the user can also close a window from the frame bar of the window, it usually does a better job to put a &quot;Close&quot; button. At least, it serves as a reminder of closing the window after viewing the content in it.

In a standard Web browser, this is typically set with a Javascript button. In the Molecular Workbench, you can insert such a button by chosing the menu &quot;Insert &gt; Activity Controller &gt; Activity Button&quot;, and on the dialog window, choose the &quot;Close this page&quot; action from the &quot;Select an action&quot; pulldown menu.

For example, this link opens a new window that carries such a button.



